Up for sale is a mint condition Russian Tiger rifle package. These rifles hardly been used, so finding one like this with the original box and accessories is getting harder and harder.  It will definitely be a nice piece in someone's collection. The rifle appears to be unfired. It's in as perfect a shape as it can be after 20 years. The finish is as close to perfect as you can get. What appears to be all the factory accessories are there including the original manual and scope. All-in-all, a great package. This package comes with the rare factory SVD buttstock instead of the usual Tiger thumbhole stocks. Very few were shipped to the States like this. The rifle is ready for a new home, don't miss this opportunity. 


For those who do not already know, these Tiger rifles are the "friendly, sporting" version of the infamous Russian Dragunov SVD sniper rifle. They have the exact same receiver and all parts interchange with the original rifle. Simply add a flashhider and a military stock set and you're very close to the original SVD rifle. The barrel is four inches shorter than the full military version, but this has little-to-no impact on the accuracy or range of the weapon. With no more of these ever coming into the country, this is a great piece to own.

title: For Sale:  GA Precision Remington 700 300 12 Egg Magnum ATACR
postcontent:
This cartridge was designed by G.A. Precision of Kansas City, Missouri and was used to test longevity of barrel steels. 
It takes the already over-bored parent case of a .30-378 Weatherby, and "super sizes" it, making it one of the fastest 30 caliber offerings available.
As with Ackley's chamber designs, there is no turning of necks or prepping of brass.  Simply load a .30-378 Weatherby Magnum case to 90%, and fireform.
To date, the best fire forming load uses Retumbo, Remington 9 1/2 Large Rifle Magnum Primers, Weatherby Brass, and the 155 grain Lapua Scenar. 
It will launch a 155 gr. Lapua Scenar at over 4000 fps with ease.  Maximum loads in 30-inch and longer barrels will produce velocities in excess of 4,100 fps.  
A rifle producing these velocities only needs 16 MOA or 4 MILs of adjustment to reach 1000 yards on target. The .300 12 Egg Magnum 
was named afterChris Matthews of Long Shot Rifles, who was an employee of GAPrecision, and a big proponent of the overbored cartridges.
At the time of this writing, GA Precision was the only known holder of a .300 12  Egg Magnum Reamer...

title: For Sale:  Tracking Point XS3 300 Win Mag Surgeon McMillan A5
postcontent:
The Tracking Point XactSystem enables you to track, tag, and hit targets at extreme ranges. The TP system calculates the following: range, pressure, drop, temp., relative humidity, spin drift, muzzle velocity, direction, barrel length and twist, cant, lock time, inclination, ballistic coefficient, drag coefficient. 
The only manual input is wind calculation. Essentially you lock on to your target with the Tag button, the TP persistently tracks your target as it moves, then when you pull the trigger the rifle won't fire until you're on target, then the XactSystem guides your shot on target. The ballistic computer in the TP scope accounts for all range and environmental factors, and it adjusts the reticle position accordingly to hit the tagged target.
It comes as a complete firing system in a custom hard case with 200 rounds of XactShot ammo, plus an iPad pre-loaded with Tracking Point apps and all the batteries, chargers, mags, cleaning supplies, and instructions you need
